programme.title: Bastille Day
programme.desc: When a reckless CIA agent and a brilliant pickpocket uncover a large-scale conspiracy, they must work together in order to take down a common enemy.

programme.title: Transformers: Dark of the Moon
programme.desc: A mysterious event from Earths past threatens to ignite a war so big that the Transformers alone will not be able to save the planet. Sam Witwicky and the Autobots must fight against the darkness to defend our world from the Decepticons all-consuming evil.

programme.title: The Dark Knight Rises
programme.desc: It has been eight years since Batman vanished into the night, turning, in that instant, from hero to fugitive. Assuming the blame for the death of DA Harvey Dent, the Dark Knight sacrificed everything for what he and Commissioner Gordon both hoped was the greater good. For a time the lie worked, as criminal activity in Gotham City was crushed under the weight of the anti-crime Dent Act. Everything will change with the arrival of a cunning cat burglar with a mysterious agenda. Far more dangerous, however, is the emergence of Bane, a masked terrorist whose ruthless plans for Gotham drive Bruce out of his self-imposed exile. Even if he dons the cape and cowl again, Batman may be no match for Bane.

programme.title: Oblivion
programme.desc: Jack Harper is the lone security repairman stationed on a desolate, nearly-ruined future Earth. When he rescues a beautiful stranger from a downed spacecraft, her arrival triggers a nonstop chain of events that forces him to question everything he knows, and leaves humanitys fate in his hands.

programme.title: Robin Hood (2010)
programme.desc: Robin Hood, the legendary figure of 13th century England, who along with his band of marauders confront corruption in the local village of Nottingham and lead an uprising against the crown that will forever alter the balance of world power. Whether regarded as thief or hero, one man from humble beginnings will become an eternal symbol of freedom for his people.

programme.title: Snakes on a Plane
programme.desc: A fast paced, edge of your seat thrill ride. FBI agent Flynn is on a mission: transport a federally protected witness from Hawaii to Los Angeles so the government can put a brutal mob boss behind bars. But, just as the plane reached 30,000 feet, hundreds of venomous snakes are unleashed, causing violent mayhem as the vicious predators attack everyone in sight. With the help of L.A.s leading snake expert on the ground, Flynn leads the other passengers on a desperate, action-packed fight for their lives.

programme.title: Spider-Man
programme.desc: After a radioactive spider bite, a nerdy teen develops keen senses and amazing strength.

programme.title: The Dark Knight
programme.desc: With the help of Lt. Jim Gordon and District Attorney Harvey Dent, Batman sets out to destroy organised crime in Gotham for good. The triumvirate proves effective, but soon find themselves prey to a rising criminal mastermind known as The Joker, who thrusts Gotham into anarchy and forces Batman closer to crossing the fine line between hero and vigilante.

programme.title: Jack Reacher
programme.desc: A military cop becomes involved in a deadly game of cat-and-mouse when five people are randomly murdered by a sniper.

programme.title: The Accountant
programme.desc: Christian Wolff is a math savant with more affinity for numbers than people. Behind the cover of a small-town CPA office, he works as a freelance accountant for some of the worlds most dangerous criminal organisations. With the Treasury Departments Crime Enforcement Division, run by Ray King, starting to close in, Christian takes on a legitimate client: a state-of-the-art robotics company where an accounting clerk has discovered a discrepancy involving millions of dollars. But as Christian uncooks the books and gets closer to the truth, it is the body count that starts to rise.

programme.title: Batman Begins
programme.desc: This story explores the origins of the Batman legend and the Dark Knights emergence as a force for good in Gotham. In the wake of his parents murder, disillusioned industrial heir Bruce Wayne travels the world seeking the means to fight injustice and turn fear against those who prey on the fearful. He returns to Gotham and unveils his alter-ego: Batman, a masked crusader who uses his strength, intellect and an array of high tech deceptions to fight the sinister forces that threaten the city.

programme.title: Geostorm
programme.desc: A system of satellites designed to protect the earth from natural disasters starts to malfunction, but who is responsible and can it be stopped?

programme.title: Interstellar
programme.desc: With our time on Earth coming to an end, a team of explorers undertakes the most important mission in human history: travelling beyond this galaxy to discover whether mankind has a future among the stars.

programme.title: The Mummy (1999)
programme.desc: Adventurer Rick OConnell and Egyptologist Evelyn Carnahan discover the lost city of Hamunaptra, and struggle to save the world from unspeakable evil after they inadvertently stumble upon a mummys tomb in 1923, and the mummy is accidentally resurrected.

programme.title: Venom
programme.desc: Eddie Brock is a broken man after he loses everything including his job and fiancee. Just when his life is at its lowest, he becomes host to an alien symbiote which results in extraordinary superpowers - transforming him into Venom. Will these powers be enough for this new lethal protector to defeat great evil forces, especially against the far stronger and more weaponized symbiote rival, Riot?

programme.title: The Meg
programme.desc: A deep-sea submersible part of an international undersea observation program has been attacked by a massive creature, previously thought to be extinct, and now lies disabled at the bottom of the deepest trench in the Pacific with its crew trapped inside. With time running out, expert deep sea rescue diver Jonas Taylor is recruited by a visionary Chinese oceanographer, against the wishes of his daughter Suyin, to save the crew and the ocean itself from this unstoppable threat: a pre-historic 75-foot-long shark known as the Megalodon. What no one could have imagined is that, years before, Taylor had encountered this same terrifying creature. Now, teamed with Suyin, he must confront his fears and risk his own life to save everyone trapped below bringing him face to face once more with the greatest and largest predator of all time.

programme.title: Scream 2
programme.desc: Away at college, Sidney Prescott thought shed finally put the shocking murders that shattered her life behind her, until a copycat killer begins acting out a real-life sequel. Now, as history eerily repeats itself, ambitious reporter Gale Weathers, Deputy Dewey and other Scream survivors find themselves trapped in a terrifyingly clever plotline where no one is safe or beyond suspicion.

programme.title: The Amazing Spider-Man 2
programme.desc: Spider-Mans greatest battle begins when an evil corporation attempts world domination by deploying an army of super villains to crush Peter Parker.

programme.title: Machete
programme.desc: Left for dead after clashing with notorious Mexican drug kingpin Torrez, Machete has escaped to Texas, looking to disappear and forget his tragic past. What he finds is a web of corruption and deceit that leaves a bullet in a senator and Machete a wanted man. Machete sets out to clear his name and expose a deep conspiracy. But standing in his way are a ruthless businessman with an endless payroll of killers, a twisted border vigilante leading a small army, and a beautiful Immigration officer torn between enforcing the law and doing what is right.

programme.title: Men in Black II
programme.desc: When a renegade Kylothian monster disguised as a lingerie model threatens the survival of the human race, the boys of the MIB get the call to step up and get busy. With their headquarters under siege and time running out, Agents K and J enlist the help of Frank the Pug and a posse of hard-living worms to help them kick some seriously sexy alien butt!

programme.title: After Earth
programme.desc: A crashlanding puts a father and son on a dangerous planet - Earth. Hunted by an alien and by evolved animal species, the pair must work together to survive.

programme.title: Suicide Squad
programme.desc: It feels good to be bad. Assemble a team of the worlds most dangerous, incarcerated supervillains, provide them with the most powerful arsenal at the governments disposal, and send them off on a mission to defeat an enigmatic, insuperable entity. US intelligence officer Amanda Waller has determined only a secretly convened group of disparate, despicable individuals with next to nothing to lose will do. Once they realise they werent picked to succeed, but chosen for their patent culpability when they inevitably fail, will the Suicide Squad resolve to die trying, or decide its everyone for themself?

programme.title: Transformers: The Last Knight
programme.desc: Humans are at war with the Transformers, and Optimus Prime is gone. The key to saving the future lies buried in the secrets of the past and the hidden history of Transformers on Earth. Now, its up to the unlikely alliance of Cade Yeager, Bumblebee, an English lord and an Oxford professor to save the world.

programme.title: Passengers
programme.desc: A spacecraft transporting thousands of people to a distant planet has a malfunction in its sleep chambers, and as a result two passengers are awakened 90 years too early.

programme.title: War Of The Worlds (2005)
programme.desc: Ray Ferrier is a working class man living in New Jersey. Hes estranged from his family, his life isnt in order, and hes too caught up with himself. But the unthinkable and ultimately the unexpected happens to him in an extraordinary sense. His small town life is shaken violently by the arrival of destructive intruders: Aliens which have come in masses to destroy the planet. As they plough through the country in a wave of mass destruction and violence, Ray must come to the defence of his children. As the world must fend for itself by a new and very advanced enemy not of this world, its inhabitants must save humanity from a far greater force than threatens to destroy it.

programme.title: Spider-Man 3
programme.desc: The web-spinning superhero must battle his own demons and a barrage of new villains including Sandman and Venom.

programme.title: Machete

programme.title: After Earth
programme.desc: A crashlanding puts a father and son on a dangerous planet - Earth. Hunted by an alien and by evolved animal species, the pair must work together to survive.

programme.title: Suicide Squad
programme.desc: It feels good to be bad. Assemble a team of the worlds most dangerous, incarcerated supervillains, provide them with the most powerful arsenal at the governments disposal, and send them off on a mission to defeat an enigmatic, insuperable entity. US intelligence officer Amanda Waller has determined only a secretly convened group of disparate, despicable individuals with next to nothing to lose will do. Once they realise they werent picked to succeed, but chosen for their patent culpability when they inevitably fail, will the Suicide Squad resolve to die trying, or decide its everyone for themself?

programme.title: Transformers: The Last Knight
programme.desc: Humans are at war with the Transformers, and Optimus Prime is gone. The key to saving the future lies buried in the secrets of the past and the hidden history of Transformers on Earth. Now, its up to the unlikely alliance of Cade Yeager, Bumblebee, an English lord and an Oxford professor to save the world.

programme.title: Passengers
programme.desc: A spacecraft transporting thousands of people to a distant planet has a malfunction in its sleep chambers, and as a result two passengers are awakened 90 years too early.

programme.title: War Of The Worlds (2005)
programme.desc: Ray Ferrier is a working class man living in New Jersey. Hes estranged from his family, his life isnt in order, and hes too caught up with himself. But the unthinkable and ultimately the unexpected happens to him in an extraordinary sense. His small town life is shaken violently by the arrival of destructive intruders: Aliens which have come in masses to destroy the planet. As they plough through the country in a wave of mass destruction and violence, Ray must come to the defence of his children. As the world must fend for itself by a new and very advanced enemy not of this world, its inhabitants must save humanity from a far greater force than threatens to destroy it.

programme.title: Spider-Man 3
programme.desc: The web-spinning superhero must battle his own demons and a barrage of new villains including Sandman and Venom.

programme.title: World War Z
programme.desc: The story revolves around United Nations employee Gerry Lane, who traverses the world in a race against time to stop a pandemic that is toppling armies and governments and threatening to decimate humanity itself.

programme.title: Bastille Day
programme.desc: When a reckless CIA agent and a brilliant pickpocket uncover a large-scale conspiracy, they must work together in order to take down a common enemy.

programme.title: Transformers: Dark of the Moon
programme.desc: A mysterious event from Earths past threatens to ignite a war so big that the Transformers alone will not be able to save the planet. Sam Witwicky and the Autobots must fight against the darkness to defend our world from the Decepticons all-consuming evil.

programme.title: The Dark Knight Rises
programme.desc: It has been eight years since Batman vanished into the night, turning, in that instant, from hero to fugitive. Assuming the blame for the death of DA Harvey Dent, the Dark Knight sacrificed everything for what he and Commissioner Gordon both hoped was the greater good. For a time the lie worked, as criminal activity in Gotham City was crushed under the weight of the anti-crime Dent Act. Everything will change with the arrival of a cunning cat burglar with a mysterious agenda. Far more dangerous, however, is the emergence of Bane, a masked terrorist whose ruthless plans for Gotham drive Bruce out of his self-imposed exile. Even if he dons the cape and cowl again, Batman may be no match for Bane.

programme.title: Oblivion
programme.desc: Jack Harper is the lone security repairman stationed on a desolate, nearly-ruined future Earth. When he rescues a beautiful stranger from a downed spacecraft, her arrival triggers a nonstop chain of events that forces him to question everything he knows, and leaves humanitys fate in his hands.

programme.title: Robin Hood (2010)
programme.desc: Robin Hood, the legendary figure of 13th century England, who along with his band of marauders confront corruption in the local village of Nottingham and lead an uprising against the crown that will forever alter the balance of world power. Whether regarded as thief or hero, one man from humble beginnings will become an eternal symbol of freedom for his people.

programme.title: Snakes on a Plane
programme.desc: A fast paced, edge of your seat thrill ride. FBI agent Flynn is on a mission: transport a federally protected witness from Hawaii to Los Angeles so the government can put a brutal mob boss behind bars. But, just as the plane reached 30,000 feet, hundreds of venomous snakes are unleashed, causing violent mayhem as the vicious predators attack everyone in sight. With the help of L.A.s leading snake expert on the ground, Flynn leads the other passengers on a desperate, action-packed fight for their lives.

programme.title: Spider-Man
programme.desc: After a radioactive spider bite, a nerdy teen develops keen senses and amazing strength.

programme.title: The Dark Knight
programme.desc: With the help of Lt. Jim Gordon and District Attorney Harvey Dent, Batman sets out to destroy organised crime in Gotham for good. The triumvirate proves effective, but soon find themselves prey to a rising criminal mastermind known as The Joker, who thrusts Gotham into anarchy and forces Batman closer to crossing the fine line between hero and vigilante.

programme.title: Jack Reacher
programme.desc: A military cop becomes involved in a deadly game of cat-and-mouse when five people are randomly murdered by a sniper.

programme.title: The Accountant
programme.desc: Christian Wolff is a math savant with more affinity for numbers than people. Behind the cover of a small-town CPA office, he works as a freelance accountant for some of the worlds most dangerous criminal organisations. With the Treasury Departments Crime Enforcement Division, run by Ray King, starting to close in, Christian takes on a legitimate client: a state-of-the-art robotics company where an accounting clerk has discovered a discrepancy involving millions of dollars. But as Christian uncooks the books and gets closer to the truth, it is the body count that starts to rise.

programme.title: Batman Begins
programme.desc: This story explores the origins of the Batman legend and the Dark Knights emergence as a force for good in Gotham. In the wake of his parents murder, disillusioned industrial heir Bruce Wayne travels the world seeking the means to fight injustice and turn fear against those who prey on the fearful. He returns to Gotham and unveils his alter-ego: Batman, a masked crusader who uses his strength, intellect and an array of high tech deceptions to fight the sinister forces that threaten the city.

programme.title: Geostorm
programme.desc: A system of satellites designed to protect the earth from natural disasters starts to malfunction, but who is responsible and can it be stopped?

programme.title: Interstellar
programme.desc: With our time on Earth coming to an end, a team of explorers undertakes the most important mission in human history: travelling beyond this galaxy to discover whether mankind has a future among the stars.

programme.title: The Mummy (1999)
programme.desc: Adventurer Rick OConnell and Egyptologist Evelyn Carnahan discover the lost city of Hamunaptra, and struggle to save the world from unspeakable evil after they inadvertently stumble upon a mummys tomb in 1923, and the mummy is accidentally resurrected.

programme.title: Venom
programme.desc: Eddie Brock is a broken man after he loses everything including his job and fiancee. Just when his life is at its lowest, he becomes host to an alien symbiote which results in extraordinary superpowers - transforming him into Venom. Will these powers be enough for this new lethal protector to defeat great evil forces, especially against the far stronger and more weaponized symbiote rival, Riot?

programme.title: The Meg
programme.desc: A deep-sea submersible part of an international undersea observation program has been attacked by a massive creature, previously thought to be extinct, and now lies disabled at the bottom of the deepest trench in the Pacific with its crew trapped inside. With time running out, expert deep sea rescue diver Jonas Taylor is recruited by a visionary Chinese oceanographer, against the wishes of his daughter Suyin, to save the crew and the ocean itself from this unstoppable threat: a pre-historic 75-foot-long shark known as the Megalodon. What no one could have imagined is that, years before, Taylor had encountered this same terrifying creature. Now, teamed with Suyin, he must confront his fears and risk his own life to save everyone trapped below bringing him face to face once more with the greatest and largest predator of all time.

Not one to miss such a grand occasion, Coras mother, Martha Levinson, makes the journey from New York with her playboy son Harold, fresh from his recent brush with the law. Both outspoken and larger-than-life, will they make an impression among certain members of Londons high society? Downstairs, Daisy gets an unexpected invitation and Carson treats the staff to a special day out. But, when the Crawleys are implicated in a scandal that threatens to engulf the monarchy, what lengths will Robert go to in order to protect the royal family, and his own?

programme.title: Beetlejuice
programme.desc: Whats a couple of stay-at-home ghosts to do when their beloved home is taken over by trendy yuppies? They call on Beetlejuice, the afterlifes freelance bio-exorcist to scare off the family - and everyone gets more than she, he or it bargains for!

programme.title: Knocked Up
programme.desc: Allison Scott is an up-and-coming entertainment journalist whose 24-year-old life is on the fast track. But it gets seriously derailed when a drunken one-night stand with slacker Ben Stone results in an unexpected pregnancy. Faced with the prospect of going it alone or getting to know the babys father, Allison decides to give the lovable layabout a chance. An overgrown kid with no desire to settle down, Ben learns he has a big decision to make with his kids mother-to-be: will he run or stay?

programme.title: Couples Retreat
programme.desc: Four bickering couples embark on a journey to a tropical island resort. While one of the couples is there to work on their marriage, the other three set out to enjoy some fun in the sun.

programme.title: Dolittle
programme.desc: After losing his wife seven years earlier, the eccentric Dr. John Dolittle, famed doctor and veterinarian of Queen Victorias England, hermits himself away behind the high walls of Dolittle Manor with only his menagerie of exotic animals for company. But when the young queen falls gravely ill, a reluctant Dolittle is forced to set sail on an epic adventure to a mythical island in search of a cure, regaining his wit and courage as he crosses old adversaries and discovers wondrous creatures.

programme.title: The Dilemma
programme.desc: A man finds out that his best friend and business partners wife may be cheating, plunging him into the moral dilemma of deciding whether to tell his friend. What ensues is comic mayhem wherein the process of uncovering lies only begets more lies.

programme.title: Holmes and Watson
programme.desc: Holmes and Watson join forces to solve a murder at Buckingham Palace. They soon realise that they only have 5760 minutes to solve the case, or the Queen will be next.

But when the championship pits Phils underdog team against the squad coached by his own domineering dad, its game on for the most uproarious mismatch of the season.

And when he meets single guy Steven Kovacs, he sees his chance for some serious male bonding. But Chips idea of friendship - which includes physical assault, a game of Porno Password and a medieval joust - may be hazardous to Stevens health. In Chips own immortal words, "I can be your best friend or your worst enemy."

programme.title: Johnny English
programme.desc: He knows no fear. He knows no danger. He knows nothing! When the priceless Crown Jewels are stolen, bumbling Johnny English is the only secret agent in the country who can solve the crime. His prime suspects: a sinister businessman and a beautiful woman with a mysterious interest in Johnnys top-secret mission. Can the clueless super spy save the day without denting the nations pride, or his super-cool Aston Martin spy car?

programme.title: Johnny English Strikes Again
programme.desc: The new adventure begins when a cyber-attack reveals the identity of all active undercover agents in Britain, leaving Johnny English as the secret services last hope. Called out of retirement, English dives head first into action with the mission to find the mastermind hacker. As a man with few skills and analogue methods, Johnny English must overcome the challenges of modern technology to make this mission a success.

programme.title: Drillbit Taylor
programme.desc: Owen Wilson stars in this riotous comedy from the producers of The 40-Year-Old Virgin and the writers of Superbad. When three young students, Ryan (Troy Gentile), Wade (Nate Hartley) and Emmit (David Dorfman) attend their first day at high school they come across school bully, Filkins (Alex Frost) who channels Hannibal Lecter. Coming up with the idea of getting some protection from this maniac, they place an ad in Soldier of Fortune magazine looking for a bodyguard. Enter Drillbit Taylor (Wilson), not the best but definitely the cheapest of the mercenaries, hit men and bodyguards who respond. Drillbit is steely, dangerous and skilled in covert black-ops and exotic martial arts; hes also a complete fraud. Taylor enrols them in physical and mental training, steeling them, and possibly himself, for the ultimate clash against the forces of evil.

programme.title: Ace Ventura: Pet Detective
programme.desc: Hes the best there is. In fact, hes the only one there is! Hes Ace Ventura Pet Detective and hes on the case to find the Miami Dolphins missing mascot and quarterback Dan Marino. He goes eyeball to eyeball with a man-eating shark, stakes out the Miami Dolphins and woos and wows the ladies. Whether hes undercover, under fire or underwater, he always gets his man or beast.

programme.title: Magic Trip
programme.desc: In 1964, Ken Kesey, the famed author of One Flew Over the Cuckoos Nest, set off on a legendary, LSD-fuelled cross-country road trip to the New York Worlds Fair. He was joined by The Merry Band of Pranksters, a renegade group of counterculture truth-seekers, including Neal Cassady, the American icon immortalised in Kerouacs On the Road. Kesey and the Pranksters intended to make a documentary about their trip, shooting hours of 16mm footage, but the film was never finished and the footage has remained virtually unseen ... until now. Oscar-winning director Alex Gibney and Alison Ellwood were given unprecedented access to this raw footage by the Kesey family. Working with the Film Foundation, and the UCLA Film Archives, they restored over 100 hours of film and audiotape to create the extraordinary, joyous, LSD-laced Magic Trip.

programme.title: Nas: Time Is Illmatic
programme.desc: Twenty years after the release of Nass groundbreaking debut album Illmatic, this prgoram takes us into the heart of his creative process. Featuring interviews with his Illmatic producers (Large Professor, Pete Rock, Q-Tip, L.E.S., and DJ Premier) and musical peers (including Pharrell Williams and Alicia Keys), this is a thrilling account of Nass evolution from a young street poet to a visionary MC.

programme.title: Tom and Jerry
programme.desc: A legendary rivalry re-emerges when Jerry moves into New York Citys finest hotel on the eve of the wedding of the century, forcing the desperate event planner to hire Tom to get rid of him. As mayhem ensues, the escalating cat-and-mouse battle soon threatens to destroy her career, the wedding, and possibly the hotel itself.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: When the evil wizard Gargamel chases the tiny blue Smurfs out of their village, they tumble from their magical world into the middle of Central Park, but they must find a way back before he tracks them down.

programme.title: Scoob!
programme.desc: "Scoob!" reveals how lifelong friends Scooby and Shaggy first met and how they joined with young detectives Fred, Velma and Daphne to form the famous Mystery Inc. Now, with hundreds of cases solved and adventures shared, Scooby and the gang face their biggest, most challenging mystery ever, a plot to unleash the ghost dog Cerberus upon the world. As they race to stop this global "dogpocalypse", the gang discovers that Scooby has a secret legacy and an epic destiny greater than anyone imagined.

programme.title: E.T. the Extra-Terrestrial
programme.desc: While visiting the Earth at Night, a group of alien botanists is discovered and disturbed by an approaching human task force. Because of the more than hasty take-off, one of the visitors is left behind. The little alien finds himself all alone on a very strange planet. Fortunately, the extra-terrestrial soon finds a friend and emotional companion in 10-year-old Elliot, who discovered him looking for food in his familys garden shed. While E.T. slowly gets acquainted with Elliots brother Michael, his sister Gertie as well as with Earth customs, members of the task force work day and night to track down the whereabouts of Earths first visitor from Outer Space.

programme.title: Spirit Untamed
programme.desc: The next chapter in this beloved franchise begins as a young girl finds a connection to her mothers legacy as a trick rider and forms a bond with a wild mustang named Spirit.

programme.title: Matilda
programme.desc: A wonderful little girl who happens to be a genius, along with her understanding teacher, outwit the worst parents and the worst school principal imaginable.

programme.title: The Pirates Who Dont Do Anything
programme.desc: Those vegie-eating boys are back. Three veggies serve as cabin boys at a pirate-themed dinner theatre, where they long to move from table service to the stage show, but their incompetence, laziness and cowardice get in the way. But when a princess drags them into the 17th century to rescue her brother, whos been kidnapped by a nefarious pirate with designs on her kingdom, they have to overcome their issues and become heroes.

programme.title: Journey 2: The Mysterious Island
programme.desc: The journey begins when young adventurer Sean receives a coded distress signal from a mysterious island where no island should exist - a place of strange life forms, mountains of gold, deadly volcanoes, and more than one astonishing secret. Unable to stop him from going, Seans new stepfather joins the quest. Together with a helicopter pilot and his beautiful, strong-willed daughter, they set out to find the island, rescue its lone inhabitant and escape before seismic shock waves force the island under the sea and bury its treasures forever.

programme.title: The Secret Garden (2020)
programme.desc: When Mary Lennoxs parents suddenly die, she is sent to live with her uncle, Archibald Craven, on his remote country estate deep in the Yorkshire moors. While exploring, she discovers a hidden magical garden.

programme.title: An American Tail
programme.desc: Fievel the mouse travels from Russia to America with his family in the late 1800s to seek freedom from cat persecution.

programme.title: An American Tail: Fievel Goes West
programme.desc: Lured out west by the crafty Cat R. Waul, Fievel joins forces with famed lawdog Wylie Blurp to thwart a sinister plot to transform unsuspecting settlers into mouse burgers!

programme.title: Captain Underpants: The First Epic Movie
programme.desc: George and Harold are fourth-grade BFFs who love dreaming up funny pranks. One day, they accidentally hypnotise their principal into believing hes a dimwitted hero named Captain Underpants. But when the new schoolteacher turns out to be a disgraced scientist bent on ridding the world of laughter, George, Harold and Captain Underpants must band together to stop his evil agenda.

programme.title: Hop
programme.desc: An egg emergency ensues when the rock n roll-loving teen son of the Easter Bunny shirks his responsibility and runs away from home.

programme.title: Pixels
programme.desc: As kids in the 1980s, Sam Brenner, Will Cooper, Ludlow Lamonsoff, and Eddie The Fire Blaster Plant saved the world thousands of times - at 25 cents a game in the video arcades. Now, theyre going to have to do it for real. When intergalactic aliens discover video feeds of classic arcade games and misinterpret them as a declaration of war, they attack the Earth, using the video games as the models for their assaults, and now, US President Cooper must call on his old-school arcade friends to save the world from being destroyed by PAC-MAN, Donkey Kong, Galaga, Centipede, and Space Invaders. Joining them is Lt Col Violet Van Patten, a specialist supplying the arcaders with unique weapons to fight the aliens.

programme.title: Babe
programme.desc: The inspirational story of a shy Yorkshire piglet who doesnt quite know his place in the world. But when Farmer Hoggett wins him at the county fair, Babe discovers that he can be anything he wants to be - even an award-winning sheepdog. With the help of a delightful assortment of barnyard friends, the heroic little pig is headed for the challenge of his life in this endearing and fun-filled tale the whole family will love.

programme.title: The Swan Princess: A Royal Wedding
programme.desc: Join Princess Odette, Prince Derek and their royal friends as they set sail for another magical adventure in the enchanted land of Cathay.

programme.title: Jumanji
programme.desc: Young Alan Parrish sits down as a young boy to play a game with his friend, Sarah, and on a roll of the dice is mysteriously transported into the strange jungle realm of Jumanji. There he remains trapped for 26 years, until two newly orphaned children, Judy and Peter, playing in the attic of Alans childhood home, free the now-adult Alan from the games clutches. But to defeat Jumanjis encroaching powers, the three reluctant players must find the now-grown Sarah and band together as a makeshift family to finish the game - before it finishes them.

programme.title: Paddington
programme.desc: This film tells the story of the comic misadventures of a young Peruvian bear who travels to the city in search of a home. Finding himself lost and alone, he begins to realise that city life is not all he had imagined until he meets the kindly Brown family who read the label around his neck that says "Please look after this bear. Thank you," and offer him a temporary haven. It looks as though his luck has changed until this rarest of bears catches the eye of a museum taxidermist.

But when a wild and dangerous alien robot lands on Earth, The President enlists this motley crew to save the world from imminent destruction.

programme.title: Jurassic Park
programme.desc: Eccentric scientist John Hammond plans to open a theme park consisting of live dinosaurs, genetically engineered from DNA. Archaeologists Alan Grant and Ellie Sattler are invited to view the park, only to find themselves being hunted when the dinosaurs break free.

programme.title: The Lost World: Jurassic Park
programme.desc: It has been four years since the disaster at Jurassic Park and two groups are in a race against time that will determine the fate of the remote islands prehistoric inhabitants.

programme.title: Jurassic Park III
programme.desc: Desperate to find their missing son, Paul and his wife Amanda trick eminent palaeontologist Dr Alan Grant into accompanying them to Isla Sorna. The small team embark on a dangerous task, searching through a deserted island inhabited by ferocious dinosaurs.

programme.title: Megamind
programme.desc: Megamind is the most brilliant super-villain the world has ever known, and the least successful. Over the years he has tried to conquer Metro City in every imaginable way. Each attempt, a colossal failure thanks to the caped superhero known as Metro Man, until the day Megamind actually defeats him in the throes of one of his botched evil plans. Suddenly, the fate of Metro City is threatened when a new villain arrives and chaos runs rampant, leaving everyone to wonder: can the worlds biggest mind actually save the day?

programme.title: Jumanji: Welcome to the Jungle
programme.desc: In the brand new adventure Jumanji: Welcome to the Jungle, the tables are turned as four teenagers are sucked into the world of Jumanji. When four high-school kids discover an old video game console with a game theyve never heard of Jumanji they are immediately drawn into the games jungle setting, literally becoming the avatars they chose: gamer Spencer becomes a brawny adventurer; football jock Fridge loses (in his words) the top two feet of his body and becomes an Einstein; popular girl Bethany becomes a middle-aged male professor; and wallflower Martha becomes a badass warrior. What they discover is that you dont just play Jumanji you must survive it. To beat the game and return to the real world, theyll have to go on the most dangerous adventure of their lives, discover what Alan Parrish left 20 years ago, and change the way they think about themselves or theyll be stuck in the game forever.

programme.title: Rise of the Billionaires
programme.desc: This closing episode bears witness to the extraordinary transformation that the billionaires have undergone these past thirty years: they are now amongst the very richest people on the planet, they can pursue their passions on such a grand scale as never seen before. Elon Musk and Jeff Bezos lock horns in a Space Race, each genuinely believing that they are saving humankind. Mark Zuckerberg desires to connect the whole world but gets embroiled in accusations of genocide and election interference, along with Google. Society at large wakes up to the power of tech and starts asking: have we lost control?

programme.desc: CNNs coverage of the Gulf War highlights Teds media empire. He buys land for environmental preservation and deepens his relationship with Jane Fonda.

programme.title: The Trouble with Kanye
programme.desc: In October 2022, Ye, formerly known as Kanye West, drew widespread condemnation after wearing a White Lives Matter T-shirt at his Paris Fashion Show. That controversy was swiftly followed up with a series of antisemitic statements on social media. With his dangerous statements making global headlines, Ye doubled down by sharing dangerous and inflammatory mistruths during a series of interviews. In the face of backlash, Ye told the paparazzi that he was planning to run for president of the United States in 2024. Unfolding against the backdrop of Yes recent behaviour and his rumoured 2024 presidential campaign, this documentary sees award-winning journalist Mobeen Azhar travel to the United States to try and discover how one of Americas most celebrated artists became a megaphone for hate and division.

programme.desc: Portillo visits a station fit for royalty in Windsor, views the Maidenhead Railway Bridge an engineering triumph built by Isambard Kingdom Brunel to span the River Thames at Maidenhead, and tries his hand at collecting the mail Victorian style on a steam-powered travelling post office.

programme.title: Great British Railway Journeys
programme.desc: Portillo tastes a Victorian superfood in Alton, explores the fascinating Whitchurch silk mill, untouched for over 150 years, and tries his hand at driving a steam train on the challenging Watercress Line.

programme.desc: Ten photos reveal John Lennons lifelong search to find his place in the world, documenting his disaffection with living the life of a Beatle and his relationship with the woman who became the love of his life, Yoko Ono.

programme.title: Musics Greatest Mysteries

programme.title: Rise of the Billionaires
programme.desc: This closing episode bears witness to the extraordinary transformation that the billionaires have undergone these past thirty years: they are now amongst the very richest people on the planet, they can pursue their passions on such a grand scale as never seen before. Elon Musk and Jeff Bezos lock horns in a Space Race, each genuinely believing that they are saving humankind. Mark Zuckerberg desires to connect the whole world but gets embroiled in accusations of genocide and election interference, along with Google. Society at large wakes up to the power of tech and starts asking: have we lost control?

programme.title: Call Me Ted
programme.desc: CNNs coverage of the Gulf War highlights Teds media empire. He buys land for environmental preservation and deepens his relationship with Jane Fonda.

programme.title: The Trouble with Kanye
programme.desc: In October 2022, Ye, formerly known as Kanye West, drew widespread condemnation after wearing a White Lives Matter T-shirt at his Paris Fashion Show. That controversy was swiftly followed up with a series of antisemitic statements on social media. With his dangerous statements making global headlines, Ye doubled down by sharing dangerous and inflammatory mistruths during a series of interviews. In the face of backlash, Ye told the paparazzi that he was planning to run for president of the United States in 2024. Unfolding against the backdrop of Yes recent behaviour and his rumoured 2024 presidential campaign, this documentary sees award-winning journalist Mobeen Azhar travel to the United States to try and discover how one of Americas most celebrated artists became a megaphone for hate and division.

programme.title: The Liquidator
programme.desc: Flea market haggler. Storage locker trader. Pawnshop owner. When it comes to moving discarded merchandise Jeff Schwarz has done it all. Jeff has bought and sold his way up the food chain to become the owner of Direct Liquidation, a 30,000-square-foot warehouse chock full of ever-changing oddities, household goods, and urban artefacts that are going to make him rich. Armed with two cell phones, a wallet full of cash and his razor-sharp negotiating skills, Jeff is on the job seven days a week trying to buy low and sell high and most importantly, keep the goods moving. This program will give you a ringside seat to Jeffs fast-paced, high-stakes, buy-and-sell world. From getting the tip and checking out the goods to making the deal and finding a buyer, youll see it all - and it isnt always pretty.

Jeff has bought and sold his way up the food chain to become the owner of Direct Liquidation, a 30,000-square-foot warehouse chock full of ever-changing oddities, household goods, and urban artefacts that are going to make him rich. Armed with two cell phones, a wallet full of cash and his razor-sharp negotiating skills, Jeff is on the job seven days a week trying to buy low and sell high and most importantly, keep the goods moving. This program will give you a ringside seat to Jeffs fast-paced, high-stakes, buy-and-sell world. From getting the tip and checking out the goods to making the deal and finding a buyer, youll see it all - and it isnt always pretty.

programme.title: The Blues Brothers
programme.desc: After the release of Jake Blues from prison, he and brother Elwood go to visit the orphanage where they were raised by nuns. programme.title: The Prince of Egypt

But the truth will ultimately set them at odds, as one becomes the ruler of the most powerful empire on earth, the other the chosen leader of his people. This inspirational movie tells the universally relatable story of how a small-town boy became one of the most iconic figures in pop culture.

programme.title: Footloose (1984)
programme.desc: Teenager Ren moves from Chicago with his family to a small town in the west, and hes in for a real case of culture shock. Ren decides that this town needs a shake up: it needs to dance.

programme.title: Piece by Piece
programme.desc: LEGO bricks tell the life story of singer, songwriter and record producer Pharrell Williams - from his childhood in Virginia to his success in the music and fashion industry.

programme.desc: Aspiring street dancer Skyler is at a major crossroads in her life. Determined to prove them all wrong, Skyler practices non-stop in Atlantas underground dance scene and catches the eye of Tyrell. He helps her take her sexy dance and hip-hop battle skills to the next level in order to achieve her dreams.

programme.title: Burlesque

Ali has a chance to make her dreams come true, if only she could make the right choices.

They have to put their quarrels behind when they find out that an adorable white bunny named Snowball is building an army of lost pets determined to take revenge.

programme.title: The Secret Life of Pets 2
programme.desc: Terrier Max is coping with some major life changes. His owner is now married and has a toddler, Liam. Max is so worried about protecting the boy that he develops a nervous tic. On a family trip to a farm, Max and mutt Duke encounter canine-intolerant cows, hostile foxes and a terrifying turkey, all of which only elevates Maxs anxiety. Luckily, Max gets some guidance from veteran farm dog Rooster, who pushes Max to ditch his neuroses, find his inner alpha and give Liam a little more freedom.

programme.title: The Town
programme.desc: A bank robber falls in love with a former robbery hostage and decides he wants out of the life. With the Feds closing in he must choose: betray his friends or lose the woman he loves.

programme.title: Wicked
programme.desc: In Oz, two clashing witches, Elphaba and Glinda, form an unlikely friendship. Elphaba, wrongly labeled wicked, seeks to expose the corrupt Wizard ruling the land.

programme.title: Daddys Home 2
programme.desc: Having finally gotten used to each others existence, Brad and Dusty must now deal with their intrusive fathers during the holidays.

programme.title: Oblivion
programme.desc: Jack Harper is the lone security repairman stationed on a desolate, nearly-ruined future Earth. When he rescues a beautiful stranger from a downed spacecraft, her arrival triggers a nonstop chain of events that forces him to question everything he knows, and leaves humanitys fate in his hands.

programme.title: The Da Vinci Code
programme.desc: A Harvard professor implicated in a murder must unravel an ancient code to expose the greatest conspiracy in history.

programme.title: The Bourne Identity
programme.desc: Pulled from the sea with two bullets in his back, Jason Bourne discovers he has the skills of a very dangerous man and no memory of his violent past. Racing to unlock the secret of his own identity, he discovers the deadly truth: hes an elite government agent. To the government, Jason Bourne isnt just their property: hes a malfunctioning $30 million weapon. Lethally trained, built to disappear, hes an agent on the run who has to be taken out. Now, the governments top operative has become its No.1 target.

programme.title: Furiosa: A Mad Max Saga
programme.desc: As the world fell, young Furiosa is snatched from the Green Place of Many Mothers and falls into the hands of a great biker horde led by the warlord Dementus. Sweeping through the Wasteland, they come across the Citadel presided over by The Immortan Joe. While the two tyrants war for dominance, Furiosa must survive many trials as she puts together the means to find her way home.

programme.title: Last Night In Soho
programme.desc: Edgar Wrights psychological thriller follows a young woman mysteriously able to enter the glamorous 1960s, where the dreams of the past splinter into something darker.

programme.title: Gabon: Earths Last Chance
programme.desc: This enviro-thriller documentary feature tells the extraordinary story of scientist Professor Lee White from Manchester, who ended up becoming the Environment Minister of Gabon in central Africa.

programme.title: The Accountant
programme.desc: Christian Wolff is a math savant with more affinity for numbers than people. Behind the cover of a small-town CPA office, he works as a freelance accountant for some of the worlds most dangerous criminal organisations. With the Treasury Departments Crime Enforcement Division, run by Ray King, starting to close in, Christian takes on a legitimate client: a state-of-the-art robotics company where an accounting clerk has discovered a discrepancy involving millions of dollars. But as Christian uncooks the books and gets closer to the truth, it is the body count that starts to rise.

programme.title: Unforgiven
programme.desc: Two retired, down-on-their-luck outlaws pick up their guns one last time to collect a bounty offered by the vengeful prostitutes of the remote Wyoming town of Big Whiskey. English Bob is an ill-fated interloper, a colourful killer-for-hire. There is also the sly and brutal local sheriff, whose brand of law enforcement ranges from unconventional to ruthless. Big trouble is coming to Big Whiskey.

programme.title: Knocked Up
programme.desc: Allison Scott is an up-and-coming entertainment journalist whose 24-year-old life is on the fast track. But it gets seriously derailed when a drunken one-night stand with slacker Ben Stone results in an unexpected pregnancy. Faced with the prospect of going it alone or getting to know the babys father, Allison decides to give the lovable layabout a chance. An overgrown kid with no desire to settle down, Ben learns he has a big decision to make with his kids mother-to-be: will he run or stay?

programme.title: Tuesday
programme.desc: A mother and her teenage daughter must confront Death when it arrives in the form of an astonishing talking bird.

programme.title: Dolittle
programme.desc: After losing his wife seven years earlier, the eccentric Dr. John Dolittle, famed doctor and veterinarian of Queen Victorias England, hermits himself away behind the high walls of Dolittle Manor with only his menagerie of exotic animals for company. But when the young queen falls gravely ill, a reluctant Dolittle is forced to set sail on an epic adventure to a mythical island in search of a cure, regaining his wit and courage as he crosses old adversaries and discovers wondrous creatures.

programme.title: AfrAId
programme.desc: The Curtis family tests a new digital assistant, AIA, which learns their behaviours and anticipates needs. But AIAs protective nature means nothing, or no one, will interfere with them.

programme.title: Venom
programme.desc: Eddie Brock is a broken man after he loses everything including his job and fiancee. Just when his life is at its lowest, he becomes host to an alien symbiote which results in extraordinary superpowers - transforming him into Venom. Will these powers be enough for this new lethal protector to defeat great evil forces, especially against the far stronger and more weaponized symbiote rival, Riot?

programme.title: Ghostbusters
programme.desc: Armed with proton packs and a new range of kick-ass weapons, the Ghostbusters battle to save the city from an uprising of mischievous ghouls.

programme.title: Ghostbusters: Afterlife
programme.desc: When a single mother and her two kids arrive in a small town, they begin to discover their connection to the original Ghostbusters and the secret legacy their grandfather left behind.

programme.title: The Amazing Spider-Man 2
programme.desc: Spider-Mans greatest battle begins when an evil corporation attempts world domination by deploying an army of super villains to crush Peter Parker.

programme.title: Lights Out
programme.desc: A homeless veteran gets caught up in the world of underground fight clubs.

programme.title: Men in Black II
programme.desc: When a renegade Kylothian monster disguised as a lingerie model threatens the survival of the human race, the boys of the MIB get the call to step up and get busy. With their headquarters under siege and time running out, Agents K and J enlist the help of Frank the Pug and a posse of hard-living worms to help them kick some seriously sexy alien butt!

programme.title: After Earth
programme.desc: A crashlanding puts a father and son on a dangerous planet - Earth. Hunted by an alien and by evolved animal species, the pair must work together to survive.

programme.title: Suicide Squad
programme.desc: It feels good to be bad. Assemble a team of the worlds most dangerous, incarcerated supervillains, provide them with the most powerful arsenal at the governments disposal, and send them off on a mission to defeat an enigmatic, insuperable entity. US intelligence officer Amanda Waller has determined only a secretly convened group of disparate, despicable individuals with next to nothing to lose will do. Once they realise they werent picked to succeed, but chosen for their patent culpability when they inevitably fail, will the Suicide Squad resolve to die trying, or decide its everyone for themself?

programme.title: Transformers: The Last Knight
programme.desc: Humans are at war with the Transformers, and Optimus Prime is gone. The key to saving the future lies buried in the secrets of the past and the hidden history of Transformers on Earth. Now, its up to the unlikely alliance of Cade Yeager, Bumblebee, an English lord and an Oxford professor to save the world.

programme.title: The Passenger
programme.desc: Randy is perfectly content fading into the background. But when his co-worker Benson goes on a sudden and violent rampage leaving a trail of destruction in his wake, Randy is forced to face his fears and confront his troubled past in order to survive.

programme.title: War Of The Worlds (2005)
programme.desc: Ray Ferrier is a working class man living in New Jersey. Hes estranged from his family, his life isnt in order, and hes too caught up with himself. But the unthinkable and ultimately the unexpected happens to him in an extraordinary sense. His small town life is shaken violently by the arrival of destructive intruders: Aliens which have come in masses to destroy the planet. As they plough through the country in a wave of mass destruction and violence, Ray must come to the defence of his children. As the world must fend for itself by a new and very advanced enemy not of this world, its inhabitants must save humanity from a far greater force than threatens to destroy it.

programme.title: Fast and Furious 5
programme.desc: Dom Toretto and Brian OConner lead a reunion of returning all-stars from every chapter of the explosive franchise built on speed to assemble for a high-stakes race that places an unlikely alliance of cops and racers in from Rio de Janeiro. The team must also defeat a corrupt businessman who wants them all dead. A dogged federal agent whose strike team tears through South America in hot pursuit, but soon has a difficult time determining the good men from the bad.

programme.title: Waterworld
programme.desc: Earth is covered with water and the human race struggles to survive on dilapidated boats and makeshift floating cities. A drifter becomes caught up in the struggle between the evil Deacon and a childs secret key to a wondrous place called "Dryland."

programme.desc: Follows the journey of Will Brown (played by Granger Smith), a once-successful country singer whose life is shattered by the sudden loss of his wife. Struggling with grief, Will distances himself from his music, his family, and his purpose, sinking into bitterness and solitude. However, when a spirited horse trainer arrives at his ranch, she begins to break down his walls, encouraging him to confront his pain and reconnect with his passion for life and music. Through a heartfelt exploration of healing, redemption, and love, Moonrise follows Wills path back to hope as he learns to rise above his past and find new meaning in his life.

programme.title: Beyond the Fire: Resilience
programme.desc: Beyond The Fire: Resilience takes an honest look at the frustrations and triumphs on the road to recovery three years after the Black Summer Bushfire Crisis. In this 1 hour special we take an exclusive look at the triumphant power of community led recovery after the catastrophic natural disaster. Set against the stunning backdrops of The Upper Murray, East Gippsland, and Alpine Shires, Australia local heroes share wisdom and insight into their recovery journey and testify through a lens of hope about how they rebuilt - physically, emotionally and mentally despite the red tape. We explore the importance of Community supporting Community to reduce the stigma around mental health and provide life saving, first hand insight on how we can potentially prevent the magnitude of The Black Summer Bushfire Crisis reoccurring. Interviews from locals and experts in the field are interlaced with breathtaking cinematography of the landscape and powerful testimonies to create a thought provoking documentary as a catalyst for change. In addressing the red tape preventing communities and individuals from moving forward, Beyond The Fire: Resilience gives voice to those crying for changes in government policy.

We read in the Bible that God often provided Divine assistance for ancient Israel in times of war, but is there archaeological evidence to support these claims? What do scholars, archaeologists and theologians have to say about some of these battles? And if God did miraculously assist the Israelites-of old, is there any proof that God still causes Israel to triumph over her enemies in modern times?

programme.title: Bible Land Passages

Read about places like Beersheba, Jericho, Jerusalem, Caesarea, and cities surrounding the Sea of Galilee, and discover that those places exist just as the Bible describes. Explore the lands of the Bible and uncover a window into the ancient past. Sift through the archaeological data, travel down the pathways of the Bible lands and traverse through the passages of its ancient cities, trade routes, and caves and understand and appreciate the challenges of life faced by Christian forbearers, and learn how God used the historical and geographic setting of the Bible lands to refine and develop their faith. Those same real places and same real settings - when examined in the modern era - can likewise become a passage for developing greater faith and devotion for God.

When she was eight years old, her mother sold her to a pedophile. After being rescued by an anti-trafficking organisation, Reaksmey found the courage to testify against her abuser in a historic trial that resulted in a 210-year prison term. With her past behind her, Reaksmey embarks on a new life in America, receiving an education and founding her own business. Now at twenty-three she is moving back to her homeland of Cambodia, relentless in her determination to never let others experience the kind of abuse that she went through.

programme.desc: Abbey, a driven executive from Boston, makes a bold move in a rare moment of vulnerability, pouring her heart into an anonymous letter about her longing for love. Sealing it in a bottle, she tosses it into Boston Harbour, never expecting it to be found. Months later, the bottle washes ashore and is discovered by Nick, the son of the CEO of Everett Valley Farms - the very company where Abbey is about to close the biggest deal of her career. When Nick returns home to help with his fathers business, he decides to reach out to the mystery woman using the email address in the letter. Unaware of each others true identities, Abbey and Nick form a growing connection online. However, in person, they find themselves clashing as theyre forced to work together on a major project. As their relationship deepens, both online and offline, theyre faced with the challenge of reconciling their professional differences with their blossoming romance.

They believed that the power of God was evident in their growing church and that His Gospel message should be spread beyond the walls of that church to the world at large. They put their faith into action and purchased airtime on the Trinity Broadcasting Network. PowerPoint Ministries was then officially launched in April 1994. Over the past 19 years, PowerPoint Ministries has grown to an expansive network of local, national, and international television and radio broadcasts. In fact, PowerPoint can be seen or heard by a potential audience of millions of television viewers and radio listeners across the United States, the United Kingdom, Australia, South Africa, Iran, Russia, Israel and more. The Ministry has a vision to glorify God by introducing Jesus Christ as Lord to as many people as possible and to develop them in Christian living using the most effective means to impact the world, making an eternal difference in this generation.

programme.desc: This program opens with a celebration of the wood-fired oven, which many Italians constructed in their backyards when they arrived in Australia. Maeve visits the inspiring Ricupero family who settled in Jarrahdale outside Perth, where they grow vegetables on a large scale and bake 140 loaves of bread every two weeks in the huge oven they built themselves - the crunchy on the outside, soft on the inside pane di casa so adored by Italians. Guy then shows a recipe for delicious bruschetta, using day-old bread. Guy joins olive oil producer Joe Grilli from Primo Estate in McLaren Vale at harvest time and learns about mixing oils for the perfect blend. Vongole harvester Tony Petruzzelli takes us to work as he rakes waist-deep in water off Adelaides outer harbour, then Sydney chef Eugenio Maiale cooks up the classic spaghetti alla vongole, the one dish that he always keeps on his menu at his popular inner-city restaurant A Tavola. For sweets, the crunchy fried biscuit cannoli filled with fresh ricotta is close to heaven, especially when its made by second-generation Sicilian sweets master Achille Mellini from Grossi Florentino.

programme.desc: Over the years, Selling Houses Australia has helped hundreds of Aussies sell their unsellable houses, but have you ever wondered what happens next? programme.desc: Young Queensland couple Doug and Yvette have lived in a shed on their idyllic 10-acre property in the Gold Coast hinterland for two years. Originally, they planned to build an architect-designed house from scratch, but the costs were too high. Not discouraged, they sought an alternative. On a whim, they bought a discarded 100-year-old Queenslander that they plan to move to their property - a journey that will cover 130km with the old house split in two, precariously carried on separate trucks. Negotiating the winding, lush hinterland is already proving to be a logistical challenge but theyre determined to make it work. The house will be lifted off the ground with a whole new level constructed underneath, along with a large contemporary pavilion that will be joined to the house as an open-space living area.

programme.title: Grand Designs Australia
programme.desc: This is an absolute stand-out in terms of its originality - incorporating a complete lifestyle sea change that revolves around a massive fibreglass shed, housing all the elements for a totally sustainable lifestyle, like animals and home-grown veggies. It also includes a stylish, two-bedroom pad for Trace and Ronnen - a couple of perfectionists. Brisbane-based architects Donovan Hill have helped the boys design this 100m long shed which includes an office, loft, stable, animal pen and garden kitchen, surrounded by internal herb and vegetable gardens. The structure will be clad in clear and opaque fibreglass with shade cloth protecting the gardens. This is truly an incredibly unique project.

programme.title: Property Brothers: Forever Home
programme.desc: After buying a house on a hill, Brian and Lily knew they had found their forever home. With plenty of room to grow into, they plan to start a family, but the choppy main floor layout is getting in the way.

programme.title: Buying and Selling

Jonathan is determined to transform their tired old property into a luxury home buyers will love, and comes up with an ingenious plan to reclaim wasted space in the kitchen. Meanwhile, a cheeky Drew shows the kids what their over-the-top wish list looks like in real life, but finding the familys dream home will require a major compromise.

programme.title: Buying and Selling
programme.desc: Nurse Jenna and firefighter Neil are ready to settle down in a home of their own, but first they have to flip his frat house. A crew of firefighters pitches in to tackle the demo, but theres shocking news for the budget when the electrical upgrade proves worse than expected. Meanwhile, Drew is determined to find a move-in ready house that checks off every item on the couples wish list.

programme.desc: North Wales couple Rebecca and Carl want to find their very own bolt hole in Gandia that will start as a holiday home but one day become a permanent home.

programme.title: A Place in the Sun
programme.desc: Lee Juggurnauth is with Carol and David, showing them five properties around southern Valencia in Spain for their budget of 225,000 pounds.

programme.title: A Place in the Sun
programme.desc: Lancashire couple Donna and Terry have been working together in their own jewellery business for the past 15 years and have decided now is the time to spend less time at work and more time in the sunshine.

programme.title: Silent Night, Fatal Night
programme.desc: When best-selling mystery author Mallory Dearborn decides to end her long-running detective franchise, her unhinged manager takes her prisoner and forces her to write a new novel during the holidays.

programme.title: Cruise Ship Murder

programme.title: Mommy Meanest
programme.desc: A teenage girl is relentlessly cyber-bullied, only to find out the horrific texts are from her own mother.

programme.title: A Daughters Nightmare
programme.desc: After the death of her husband, Ariels mother Dana finds a friend in the mysterious Adam. When Danas health starts to fail, Ariel suspects Adam might not have the best of intentions.

programme.title: Trapped in the Rocky Mountains
programme.desc: Lured into an unwelcome reunion at a vacant ski lodge, former college friends find themselves in a fight for their lives when they become the target of an unseen adversary.

programme.title: Sisters
programme.desc: A reporter who witnesses a brutal murder becomes entangled in a mystery involving conjoined twins who were separated at birth.

programme.title: Britney Ever After
programme.desc: This is the tumultuous true story of Britney Jean Spears, one of the bestselling teenage music artists of all-time, whose dating life and public emotional breakdowns were the subjects of a worldwide media frenzy. By the age of 21, Britney Spears already had a number one platinum, debut album, a cover on Rolling Stone, a record-breaking second album, and international superstardom. Success in her personal life, however, would be much harder to achieve. A well-publicized romance and break-up with Justin Timberlake, a three-day marriage to a childhood sweetheart, and an ill-fated marriage to back-up dancer Kevin Federline made for a chaotic contrast to her record-setting music career.

programme.title: The Killer Inside: The Ruth Finley Story
programme.desc: Ruth and her husband, Eds, tranquil life in Wichita, Kansas is suddenly turned upside down when Ed suffers a heart attack. As Ed fights for his life in the hospital, Ruth starts to receive mysterious threats, leaving her in a state of panic.

programme.title: A Lifeguards Obsession
programme.desc: When a lonely, awkward lifeguard saves a well-known woman from drowning, he believes hes earned a place in her life and in her heart.

programme.title: Couples Retreat Murder
programme.desc: Becky and Jim head to a remote couples retreat to try and save their marriage. However, when a guest goes missing and their host is found dead, they start to wonder who else theyre trapped with.

programme.title: Murder Below Deck
programme.desc: When Lauren gives up the corporate life and a cheating boyfriend, she joins her best friend from college working aboard a luxury yacht in the South Pacific.

programme.title: Dying to Win
programme.desc: A gold medal gymnast is catapulted back into the spotlight when she finds her mother and step dad murdered in the family home.

programme.title: The Girl Who Wasnt Dead
programme.desc: 15-year-old Erica vanishes, believed a victim of a serial killer, but emerges at her murder trial 3 years later, having run away to live secretly with her older boyfriend near her mothers home, banned from seeing him.

programme.title: Hider in My House
programme.desc: Molly Bachman, a young best-selling author buys the apartment of her dreams in the city. As she settles in, ready to start work on her next novel, strange sounds and bumps in the night begin to alarm her, along with the feeling of being watched and followed. As she discovers the dark history of the apartment, she eventually discovers a horrifying secret - a hidden entrance to another abandoned apartment behind the walls. What lies behind those walls leads to a shocking revelation.

programme.title: How to Live Your Best Death
programme.desc: Hoping to go after her dreams, Kristin hires Ashley, a life coach who promises to help her reach her full potential. However, things take a turn when unconventional methods start to wreak havoc,

programme.title: Dying For A Crown
programme.desc: Lydia moves to LA with her daughter Elle under mysterious circumstances, becoming the assistant principal at Bellview High where Elle is a senior. With her mother by her side, Elle wont stop to become homecoming queen and gain popularity.

programme.title: Murder in Nashville
programme.desc: A woman gets swept up in a whirlwind romance with the son of a wealthy power player in the country music scene.

programme.title: Black Girl Missing
programme.desc: Cheryls daughter goes missing and is nowhere to be found. Authorities and the media dismiss her as a runaway while they focus on another missing girl, who is white.

programme.title: Single Black Female
programme.desc: Monica is a young host of one of LAs top morning shows. Reeling from the death of her beloved father and the breakup she just suffered, shes ready to focus on moving forward with her life, and channelling all of her energy into getting the new hosting gig on the afternoon talk show at her station. She gets a new assistant, Simone, a beautiful biracial woman who is new in town and so excited to be supporting Monica. They become close quickly, with Simone moving in next door, and engraining herself into Monicas life. But underneath Simones sweet exterior lies a woman who harbors a dark secret, and is determined to become closer than close to Monica, whether she likes it or not! As time goes on, and Simone becomes more and more enmeshed in Monicas life, Monica starts to pick up on the cracks in Simones shiny facade. As she tries to pull back from Simone, Monica and those around her begin to fear that it may be too late - and even worse, that Simone may have had something to do with the death of her father and collapse of her relationship! Monica decides to sever ties with Simone once and for all, however, Simone has other plans. Will Monica get her life back, or will Simone succeed in taking over Monicas life for good?

programme.title: Trapped in Her Dorm Room
programme.desc: College student Erin becomes trapped in her dorm room during Spring Break when a classmates harmless adoration turns into a dangerous obsession.

programme.title: Stalked by My Amish Boyfriend
programme.desc: Carly develops a relationship with Abram, a young Amish man. Their seemingly innocent courtship soon takes a dark turn when Abram refuses to return home.

programme.title: A Deadly Threat to My Family
programme.desc: Marielle becomes suspicious when her sister-in-law escapes from a cult and seeks refuge at her home. When another cult member shows up on her doorstep, she fears her daughter is their next target.

programme.title: My Child has My Doctors Face
programme.desc: Jessica discovers that his biological father is actually her fertility doctor, she teams up with another one of the doctors clients to bring him to justice.

programme.title: My Landlord Wants Me Dead
programme.desc: A college dropout unwittingly puts her own life at stake when she investigates a series of strange and terrifying events at her aunts secluded ranch house.

programme.title: Non-Stop
programme.desc: Having been jilted at the altar, a literary aide to a controversial author thinks nothing of a fleeting liaison with a man she meets on a business flight.

programme.title: Crowdsource Murder
programme.desc: A friend encourages Monica to start a crowdsource fund to pay for her daughters hospital bills. However, when a seemingly generous man donates more and more money, she begins to question his motives.

programme.title: Girl in the Basement
programme.desc: Inspired by true events, this is the story of Sarah, a teenager imprisoned by her father in the basement of their family home for over twenty years. The father told his wife and other children that Sarah had run away to be with a boyfriend the family disapproved of. Meanwhile, as the years went by, he would secretly visit her in the basement, raping her there while her mother and siblings continued living upstairs. Sarah gave birth alone in the basement to several children. Her father let her raise one there but brought the others upstairs, claiming to his wife that Sarah has left the grandchildren on their doorstep. When Sarah finally escapes, the family learns the devastating truth about what had been going on for years right beneath their feet.

programme.desc: When two best friends hiking the Grand Canyon trust an experienced hiking guide to bring them on an off trail adventure, things go south when he takes them captive, and they have to fight both man and nature to make it out.

programme.desc: Fleeing her abusive ex, Jess hires a boat to Canada, but when it sinks, shes rescued by a reclusive lighthouse keeper. As she heals, Jess realises shes fallen into another trap.

At first, the home of an 80-year-old widow goes up in flames. Ten days later, an assailant seriously beats an elderly couple and sets fire to their living room. Another fire leaves a 72-year-old woman dead in her mobile home. And days later, a 79-year-old woman is brutally raped before her mobile home is torched. With all signs pointing to a serial killer with a taste for elderly women and fire, local and state police join forces with the FBI. And although there are several suspects, investigators find little evidence among the ashes to build a case. That is, until the killer strikes again. Can investigators connect the dots and track down the culprit?

programme.title: Murder at My Door
programme.desc: Audrey and Eric Hingston, 81 and 83, enjoy the twilight of their happy marriage in their cosy home, until Eric is brutally stabbed to death during a supposed burglary in 2003.

programme.title: The Real Manhunter
programme.desc: Following ex-detective Colin Sutton, a former senior investigating officer with the Metropolitan Police, as he looks back at his most important cases and the investigations that solved them.

programme.title: When Missing Turns to Murder
programme.desc: British true crime documentary series using powerful and emotional testimony from families and friends when a missing persons enquiry turns into a murder investigation.

programme.title: The First 48
programme.desc: Cincinnati Homicide Detective Kurt Ballman investigates a brutal beating death in the close-knit East End neighbourhood. In Memphis, Lieutenant Toney Armstrong and Sergeant Mason use surveillance footage to track down the killer of local teenager.

programme.title: Bloodline Detectives
programme.desc: On October 9th, 1980, in Santee, San Diego, the neighbours of 20-year-old college student Michelle Wyatt hear screams coming from her condo, but fail to investigate.

programme.title: Cold Blood
programme.desc: When the nude body of a young woman is found in an abandoned orchard, all of Grand Rapids, Michigan, is on edge. After all, this is Middle America and murders like this dont happen here. Even worse, the teenage girl was strangled. It takes a few days for police to identify her as 15-year-old Deanna Gillean, a popular and promising high school student from a rundown part of town. The police quickly hone in on her father, Sam Gillean a man with a serious drinking problem. After all, he and Deanna fought the night she disappeared, and he failed to report her missing for two days. Her brother and his rowdy friends, and a local sex offender are also on the list of suspects. But with almost no evidence and leads that go nowhere, the mystery lies dormant for almost a decade. That is, until a grand jury dusts off the case and discovers the truth had been there all along.

programme.title: Cops Reloaded
programme.desc: Cops Reloaded revisits some of the most memorable suspects, car chases and action-packed moments from televisions popular reality program.

programme.title: Hitlers Handmaidens
programme.desc: Explores the women who took Hitler under their wing and trained him in the methods of high society to launch him to power, only to be left behind once he achieved it.

programme.title: Rise Of The Dictators
programme.desc: Rise of the Dictators is the story of Adolf Hitler, Benito Mussolini, and Josef Stalin; but also reveals those strong men, autocrats, and despots that followed in their footsteps.

programme.title: American Dynasty
programme.desc: Explores the evolving narrative of America through the stories of some of the nations most famous families.

programme.title: Historys Raiders
programme.desc: In November 1942, British SOE (Special Operations Executive) agents and Greek resistance fighters (andartes) attacked the Gorgopotamos railway bridge in the heart of Greece, where up to 50 trains crossed daily en route to the Port of Piraeus to supply Rommel in North Africa. While andartes battled Italian forces defending the bridge, the SOE laid explosives under the bridge. Computer graphics and dramatic recreations reveal the enormous explosion and devastation the successful Allied raid caused.

programme.title: Dogfights
programme.desc: Its where a pilot cannot afford to make a mistake but where dogfights are so often drawn. This is the grim and grisly reality of low-level dogfighting.

programme.title: Secrets of World War II
programme.sub-title: The Cruise of the Secret Raiders
programme.desc: The fascinating story of the secret, heavily armed cargo ships deployed by the Germans which were, in reality, designed to sink Allied merchant ships as well as refuelling German U-boats and warships.

programme.title: History of Warfare
programme.desc: Delve into the economic and political roots of this terrible conflict. This program details the struggle for political, economic and colonial supremacy during the early 1900s through to the horrors of the trenches, the rise of Bolshevism and the peace of 1918. From the fateful shot of the assassins gun at Sarajevo, to Armistice Day 1918, when the guns finally fell silent on the nightmare of the trenches, this is the tragic story of the conflict remembered by history as the Great War.

programme.title: Time Team
programme.desc: The team is back for another series. At low tide each day, near Vauxhall Bridge in London, the Thames reveals the tops of a mysterious group of prehistoric timbers buried on the shore in central London. Tony Robinson and the team have just two hours a day of frantic digging, fighting against the tide for three days to excavate at least one timber. In this race against time, thats more desperate than usual, the team piece together a picture of life beside the river 4000 years ago and succeed in revealing the fascinating secrets of these ancient timbers.
